## 📋 Overview

**Feature:** AMS Findings Panel on Farmer Dashboard
**Module:** Farmer Dashboard — AMS Findings Panel
**Round:** Round 1
**Environment:** CENTEST
**Application:** Basic Income Support for Sustainability (BISS)
**Created by:** Aniket Pathare | aniket.pathare@government.ie
**Date:** 28-Apr-2026

**Context:**
The AMS (Area Monitoring System) monitors land parcels declared under BISS using satellite imagery.
When potential non-compliance is detected on a parcel (e.g. Artificial Surface, crop mismatch), the
system generates a Red AMS finding for the herd. These findings are surfaced on the Farmer Dashboard
as a dedicated AMS Findings panel, prompting the farmer or agent to respond before the deadline.

**Important — Date Change from Last Year:**
The deadline message in the AMS Findings panel has been updated for 2026.

- 2026 message (individual / primary partner): **“You have until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications”**
- 2026 message (non-primary partner): **“The Primary Partner has until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications”**
  Both messages must be verified against last year’s wording to confirm they have been updated correctly.

